# META.a2ml — Echidnabot meta-level information
[metadata]
version = "0.1.0"
last-updated = "2026-04-24"

[project-info]
license = "PMPL-1.0-or-later"
author = "Jonathan D.A. Jewell (hyperpolymath)"

[architecture-decisions]
# ADRs listed chronologically. Use `status = "superseded"` when replacing.

[[architecture-decisions.decision]]
id           = "ADR-001"
date         = "2026-04-24"
status       = "accepted-temporary"
title        = "Native MCP server (echidnabot-mcp) as documented BoJ-only-MCP exception"
context      = """
Estate policy (memory: feedback_boj_only_mcp) requires all MCP tools to route
through the BoJ server. BoJ is currently unreachable on this workstation: its
V-lang adapter was removed during the V-lang ban (2026-04-10) and the Zig
replacement at boj-server/adapter/zig/src/ is empty. Package 7 needs MCP
exposure so echidnabot is directly callable by AI assistants — waiting for the
BoJ Zig rewrite would indefinitely block the double-loop actuation work.
"""
decision     = """
Ship a standalone binary `echidnabot-mcp` (src/bin/mcp_server.rs) implementing
MCP JSON-RPC 2.0 over stdio with four tools: suggest_tactics,
record_tactic_outcome, list_outcome_history, corpus_refresh. The BoJ-only rule
remains canonical; this is a single-binary documented exception, not a policy
revision.
"""
consequences = """
Positive: Package 7 double-loop actuation unblocked; echidnabot directly
testable by Claude Desktop / Claude Code. Tool logic (Reranker, CorpusDelta)
stays in the library crate, so it is reusable when the cartridge is restored.

Negative: Second MCP surface to maintain until retirement; drift risk if the
BoJ revival lags. Mitigated by: (a) retirement plan in
docs/MCP-TEMPORARY-EXCEPTION.adoc; (b) project memory
project_boj_mcp_temporary_exception.md; (c) no new standalone MCP servers
green-lit by this exception.
"""
retirement   = """
When the BoJ Zig adapter lands: port the four tool handlers into the existing
boj-server/cartridges/echidna-llm-mcp/ cartridge, remove the [[bin]] entry
from Cargo.toml, delete src/bin/mcp_server.rs, delete
docs/MCP-TEMPORARY-EXCEPTION.adoc, and delete the project memory.
"""

[development-practices]
versioning = "SemVer"
documentation = "AsciiDoc"
build-tool = "just"

[maintenance-axes]
scoping-first = true
axis-1 = "must > intend > like"
axis-2 = "corrective > adaptive > perfective"
axis-3 = "systems > compliance > effects"
